# 2026-05-13 01:46:21.750616
+you must do this, if you have any question or information you need ask before continuing: ---
+
+## PROGRAMMING DEPARTMENT — DELIVERABLE: VN-PROJECT BASE STRUCTURE
+
+---
+
+## PART 1 — TERMUX: REPOSITORY SETUP
+
+Execute these commands in order. Each is a single, complete command.
+
+**1. Update package list and install required tools**
+```bash
+pkg update && pkg upgrade -y
+```
+
+**2. Install Git**
+```bash
+pkg install git -y
+```
+
+**3. Navigate to home directory**
+```bash
+cd ~
+```
+
+**4. Create the project folder**
+```bash
+mkdir vn-project
+```
+
+**5. Enter the project folder**
+```bash
+cd vn-project
+```
+
+**6. Initialize Git repository**
+```bash
+git init
+```
+
+**7. Set Git identity (replace with your values)**
+```bash
+git config user.name "YourName"
+```
+
+```bash
+git config user.email "your@email.com"
+```
+
+---
+
+## PART 2 — FOLDER STRUCTURE CREATION
+
+Execute in order from inside `~/vn-project/`.
+
+**8. Create all project directories**
+```bash
+mkdir -p game images/bg images/sprites images/ui audio/music audio/sfx fonts
+```
+
+**Complete structure this produces:**
+```
+vn-project/
+├── game/
+│   ├── script.rpy
+│   ├── characters.rpy
+│   ├── variables.rpy
+│   ├── screens.rpy
+│   └── options.rpy
+├── images/
+│   ├── bg/
+│   ├── sprites/
+│   └── ui/
+├── audio/
+│   ├── music/
+│   └── sfx/
+├── fonts/
+├── .gitignore
+└── PROJECT.md
+```
+
+**9. Create .gitignore**
+```bash
+cat > .gitignore << 'EOF'
+# Ren'Py cache and build output
+game/cache/
+game/saves/
+*.rpyc
+*.rpymc
+*.pyc
+__pycache__/
+
+# Android build artifacts
+*.apk
+*.aab
+rapt/
+
+# OS junk
+.DS_Store
+Thumbs.db
+EOF
+```
+
+*Reason: `.rpyc` files are compiled from source at runtime and must not be tracked.*
+
+**10. Create PROJECT.md placeholder**
+```bash
+cat > PROJECT.md << 'EOF'
+# vn-project
+Master document lives in this file. See AI Context Prompt section for full project context.
+EOF
+```
+
+---
+
+## PART 3 — BASE .RPY FILES
+
+Execute each block in order.
+
+---
+
+**11. options.rpy**
+```bash
+cat > game/options.rpy << 'EOF'
+## options.rpy
+## Global Ren'Py configuration. Edit here to change engine-level settings.
+
+define config.name = "Camp Adventure"
+
+define config.version = "0.0.1"
+
+## Default window resolution. Can be changed before first launch.
+define config.screen_width = 1280
+define config.screen_height = 720
+
+## Save directory name on the player's device.
+define config.save_directory = "vn-project"
+
+## Window icon. Replace with final asset when available.
+# define config.window_icon = "images/ui/icon.png"
+
+## Skip transition time when developing. Set False for production.
+define config.developer = True
+
+## Default language.
+define config.language = None
+EOF
+```
+
+---
+
+**12. variables.rpy**
+```bash
+cat > game/variables.rpy << 'EOF'
+## variables.rpy
+## All global variables, flags, and relationship values are defined here.
+## This is the single source of truth for game state.
+
+## ── PROTAGONIST ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+
+default protagonist_name = "Alex"
+default protagonist_species = "Unknown"
+
+## ── RELATIONSHIP POINTS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+## One variable per character. Invisible to the player.
+## Convention: rel_[character_id]
+## Range: No hard cap. Narrative gates defined per character in their route.
+
+## Placeholder characters (replace IDs when characters are named)
+default rel_char1 = 0
+default rel_char2 = 0
+default rel_char3 = 0
+default rel_char4 = 0
+
+## ── BINARY FLAGS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+## True/False variables that permanently open or close story branches.
+## Convention: flag_[description]
+
+## Example flags (expand as narrative is written)
+default flag_arrived_at_camp = False
+default flag_first_day_complete = False
+
+## ── RANDOMNESS FLAGS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+## Randomness is rolled at game start and stored here.
+## This ensures consistency within a single playthrough.
+
+## Active characters this playthrough (populated on new game)
+default active_characters = []
+
+## Random event pool seed (set at new game start)
+default event_seed = 0
+
+## ── DAY TRACKING ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+
+default current_day = 1
+default max_days = 14  ## Default. Randomized at game start within design range.
+EOF
+```
+
+---
+
+**13. characters.rpy**
+```bash
+cat > game/characters.rpy << 'EOF'
+## characters.rpy
+## All Character() definitions live here.
+## Dialogue style, name display, and color are set per character.
+
+## ── NARRATOR ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+
+define narrator = Character(None, kind=nvl)
+
+## ── PROTAGONIST ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+## Protagonist name is dynamic (set by player at game start).
+
+define mc = Character("[protagonist_name]", color="#f5e6c8")
+
+## ── PLACEHOLDER CHARACTERS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
+## Replace display names, colors, and IDs when characters are finalized.
+## Color codes should match each character's palette accent.
+
+define char1 = Character("Char1", color="#a8d8a8")
+define char2 = Character("Char2", color="#f9c784")
+define char3 = Character("Char3", color="#c3aed6")
+define char4 = Character("Char4", color="#f28b82")
+
+## ── ADD NEW CHARACTERS BELOW THIS LINE ───────────────────────────────────────
+EOF
+```
+
+---
+
+**14. screens.rpy**
+```bash
+cat > game/screens.rpy << 'EOF'
+## screens.rpy
+## UI screen definitions. All custom screens are written here.
+## Ren'Py's default screens are used until replaced with final UI.
+
+## ── MAIN MENU ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+
+screen main_menu():
+    tag menu
+
+    ## Background (replace with final UI asset)
+    add "#1a1a1a"
+
+    vbox:
+        xalign 0.5
+        yalign 0.5
+        spacing 20
+
+        text "Camp Adventure" size 48 color "#f5e6c8" xalign 0.5
+
+        textbutton "New Game" action Start() xalign 0.5
+        textbutton "Load Game" action ShowMenu("load") xalign 0.5
+        textbutton "Quit" action Quit() xalign 0.5
+
+## ── HUD / DAY DISPLAY ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+## Shown during gameplay. Displays current day.
+
+screen hud():
+    frame:
+        xalign 1.0
+        yalign 0.0
+        xoffset -10
+        yoffset 10
+        text "Day [current_day] / [max_days]" size 20 color "#f5e6c8"
+
+## ── ADD NEW SCREENS BELOW THIS LINE ─────────────────────────────────────────
+EOF
+```
+
+---
+
+**15. script.rpy**
+```bash
+cat > game/script.rpy << 'EOF'
+## script.rpy
+## Main game script. All labels and scene flow are written here.
+## Characters, variables, and screens are defined in their respective files.
+
+## ── GAME START ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+
+label start:
+
+    ## Roll randomness values for this playthrough
+    $ event_seed = renpy.random.randint(1000, 9999)
+    $ max_days = renpy.random.randint(14, 28)
+
+    ## Mark arrival
+    $ flag_arrived_at_camp = True
+
+    ## ── PROTAGONIST SETUP ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+    ## TODO: Replace with player name/species input screen
+
+    $ protagonist_name = "Alex"
+    $ protagonist_species = "Placeholder"
+
+    ## ── SCENE: ARRIVAL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+
+    scene black with fade
+
+    show screen hud
+
+    narrator "The bus pulls up to a long dirt road. Through the window, you can see wooden cabins, a lake, and a big painted sign."
+
+    narrator "You have arrived at camp."
+
+    ## TODO: Add arrival scene dialogue and sprite/background assets
+
+    jump day_loop
+
+## ── DAY LOOP ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+
+label day_loop:
+
+    ## End condition
+    if current_day > max_days:
+        jump ending
+
+    ## TODO: Add daily event selection logic here
+    ## This is where randomized events will be called per day
+
+    ## Advance day
+    $ current_day += 1
+
+    jump day_loop
+
+## ── ENDING ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+
+label ending:
+
+    hide screen hud
+
+    scene black with fade
+
+    narrator "Summer is over."
+
+    narrator "You wave goodbye as the bus pulls away."
+
+    ## TODO: Add ending variations based on relationship values and flags
+
+    return
+EOF
+```
+
+---
+
+## PART 4 — GIT: INITIAL COMMIT AND PUSH
+
+**16. Stage all files**
+```bash
+git add .
+```
+
+**17. Initial commit**
+```bash
+git commit -m "init: base project structure and skeleton .rpy files"
+```
+
+**18. Set default branch to main**
+```bash
+git branch -M main
+```
+
+**19. Add remote (create the repo on GitHub first, then run this)**
+```bash
+git remote add origin https://github.com/YOURUSERNAME/vn-project.git
+```
+
+**20. Push to GitHub**
+```bash
+git push -u origin main
+```
+
+*Reason: HTTPS is used instead of SSH because SSH key setup in Termux requires additional configuration. If SSH is already configured, substitute the SSH remote URL.*
+
+---
+
+

